4. What is the ROC-AUC curve?

ROC plots TPR vs FPR at different thresholds

AUC (Area Under Curve) indicates model performance

AUC = 1 â†’ perfect

AUC = 0.5 â†’ random guessing

5. What is the confusion matrix?

A 2Ã—2 table:

	Predicted 0	Predicted 1
Actual 0	TN	FP
Actual 1	FN	TP
6. What happens if classes are imbalanced?

Problems:

Model predicts majority class

Accuracy becomes misleading

Solutions:

Class weights (class_weight="balanced")

Oversampling (SMOTE)

Undersampling

Precision/Recall or ROC-AUC instead of accuracy

7. How do you choose the threshold?

Increase threshold â†’ higher precision, lower recall

Decrease threshold â†’ higher recall, lower precision

Choose based on business goal:

Medical â†’ recall

Fraud detection â†’ precision

8. Can logistic regression be used for multi-class problems?

Yes.
Scikit-learn uses:

One-vs-Rest (OvR) â†’ default

Multinomial logistic regression â†’ with solver='lbfgs'